1
00:00:05,297 --> 00:00:08,592
Stars are somehow fascinating.
Sometimes a criminal, sometimes an actor...

2
00:00:08,676 --> 00:00:10,261
A strange code from the Professor.

3
00:00:10,344 --> 00:00:11,512
The Detective Boys face an unexpected struggle.

4
00:00:11,887 --> 00:00:13,597
Who will be the first to solve it?

5
00:00:13,848 --> 00:00:15,266
See through the one and only truth.

6
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:16,976
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

7
00:00:17,059 --> 00:00:19,103
His name is Detective Conan!

8
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:29,000
The Surprising Shrine Torii Gate Code (Part 2)

9
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:25,192
♪~♪

10
00:01:49,944 --> 00:01:55,950
♪~♪

11
00:01:57,326 --> 00:02:01,247
One hot summer day, we came to collect insects.

12
00:02:01,831 --> 00:02:04,416
The Professor gave us a code quiz
indicating the location of a treasure—

13
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:07,294
called "Marumushini Tento."

14
00:02:08,045 --> 00:02:10,673
Even I couldn't solve it.

15
00:02:11,507 --> 00:02:14,593
Meanwhile, from Ran and Sonoko,
who were spending time at the beach—

16
00:02:14,677 --> 00:02:16,345
at the hotel where they were staying—

17
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:19,473
we received word that a murder had occurred.

18
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:25,479
Sonoko said that on the window glass
of the hotel room where that man was murdered—

19
00:02:25,563 --> 00:02:28,566
there were strange characters written.

20
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:30,359
Huh? Strange characters?

21
00:02:30,442 --> 00:02:33,070
Yeah, like a code...

22
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,698
So, who found the body?

23
00:02:36,031 --> 00:02:39,702
The three friends of the murdered man,
Miyama-san.

24
00:02:40,536 --> 00:02:43,038
They all had a dinner appointment, but

25
00:02:43,122 --> 00:02:44,206
Miyama-san didn't

26
00:02:44,290 --> 00:02:45,583
show up,

27
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:47,835
so the three went to his room.

28
00:02:47,918 --> 00:02:49,461
The key was left in the lock,

29
00:02:49,545 --> 00:02:51,589
and when they went inside,
the window glass was broken,

30
00:02:51,672 --> 00:02:54,758
and Miyama-san was collapsed beside it—

31
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:57,052
that's what they testified to the police.

32
00:02:57,970 --> 00:02:59,722
After that, we...

33
00:03:00,598 --> 00:03:01,807
Then, could it be—

34
00:03:01,891 --> 00:03:04,977
that "Tento" in this code
means the Tento (Floating Lantern) Festival?

35
00:03:05,561 --> 00:03:09,440
Even if that's it, the meaning
of "Marumushi" before it is still...

36
00:03:10,065 --> 00:03:14,862
That area does have a hot spring
called Marumushi Hot Spring.

37
00:03:15,571 --> 00:03:17,740
Light the Marumushi... Huh?

38
00:03:17,823 --> 00:03:19,199
Does it mean turn on the light?

39
00:03:34,632 --> 00:03:38,552
Hey? There are a lot of people.

40
00:03:38,636 --> 00:03:41,013
Maybe there's a gathering.

41
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:44,058
No way, take a good look.

42
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:45,935
Everyone's holding a washbowl, right?

43
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:48,270
Ah, you're right.

44
00:03:48,729 --> 00:03:51,523
Probably, the village bought the ruined inn

45
00:03:51,607 --> 00:03:53,776
and they're using it as a public bath.

46
00:03:54,193 --> 00:03:55,569
I see.

47
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:58,781
Public bath? Public bath...

48
00:03:59,448 --> 00:04:01,617
Could this "Tento"—

49
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:03,911
actually mean public bath?

50
00:04:03,994 --> 00:04:05,496
Um, Genta-kun,

51
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:08,624
no matter how you look at it,
this "Te" doesn't look like "Se."

52
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,043
And it's not about lighting either.

53
00:04:11,126 --> 00:04:13,045
There's no "U" after "Tento."

54
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:15,214
Ugh.

55
00:04:15,673 --> 00:04:17,716
Ah, damn it!

56
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:19,635
I don't get it anymore.

57
00:04:19,969 --> 00:04:23,305
Hey, Genta, don't lie down in frustration.

58
00:04:23,847 --> 00:04:25,891
I'm not frustrated.

59
00:04:25,975 --> 00:04:27,726
The Professor said,

60
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:32,314
if you lie down and think carefully,
you might figure it out.

61
00:04:32,398 --> 00:04:33,899
Even so...

62
00:04:33,983 --> 00:04:36,527
Come to think of it, Ai-chan also said,

63
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:40,948
if you absolutely can't figure it out,
wash your face and start over.

64
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:43,909
Well, since there's a public bath,

65
00:04:43,993 --> 00:04:46,954
shall we wash our faces and bodies
and refresh ourselves?

66
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:48,288
Ah... that sounds good.

67
00:04:49,415 --> 00:04:50,416
It's useless.

68
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:52,418
Huh? Ai-chan.

69
00:04:52,751 --> 00:04:56,171
Going to that inn is pointless.
There's nothing there.

70
00:04:56,255 --> 00:04:58,257
Hey, do something about it.

71
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,217
Come on, Professor, just tell us.

72
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,344
Where is the treasure?

73
00:05:02,428 --> 00:05:03,887
Please, tell us.

74
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:07,808
Well, I suppose I could tell you.

75
00:05:07,891 --> 00:05:09,643
If someone gives up.

76
00:05:09,893 --> 00:05:11,186
Eh?

77
00:05:11,729 --> 00:05:12,730
Eh?

78
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:14,314
Who would do that?

79
00:05:14,398 --> 00:05:15,983
Ah.

80
00:05:16,275 --> 00:05:17,317
A mail.

81
00:05:19,236 --> 00:05:20,654
From Sonoko.

82
00:05:20,904 --> 00:05:25,492
Huh? I thought her phone and bag
were snatched by a bag-snatcher...

83
00:05:26,285 --> 00:05:27,411
Hmm?

84
00:05:28,078 --> 00:05:30,497
"I found a bag on the roadside—"

85
00:05:30,581 --> 00:05:33,000
"There's nothing inside
to identify the owner,"

86
00:05:33,459 --> 00:05:35,044
"so for the time being,
I'm emailing the—"

87
00:05:35,127 --> 00:05:37,087
"most recent recipient recorded—"

88
00:05:37,171 --> 00:05:40,632
"in the cell phone that was in the bag."

89
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,926
"I would like to return this bag,"

90
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:47,056
"so I would appreciate it
if you could tell me your address and name."

91
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:48,974
Seems like that bag-snatcher

92
00:05:49,058 --> 00:05:51,935
took the wallet and threw away the bag.

93
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,646
But if they're going to do that,

94
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:58,067
why not just ask for the owner's
address and name?

95
00:05:58,484 --> 00:06:00,861
And why specifically email?

96
00:06:00,944 --> 00:06:02,112
Check the call log—

97
00:06:02,196 --> 00:06:04,823
wouldn't it be faster to call someone?

98
00:06:06,325 --> 00:06:07,868
It's surrender, right?

99
00:06:07,951 --> 00:06:08,952
Eh?

100
00:06:09,495 --> 00:06:11,330
Ah, hey... hey, wait a minute.

101
00:06:13,415 --> 00:06:17,252
More importantly, if you find a bag,
you should turn it in to the police first!

102
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:19,922
Ah... hello, Ran?

103
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:22,007
I just got an email from someone
who found Sonoko's bag,

104
00:06:22,091 --> 00:06:23,509
but...

105
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:25,594
Eh, really?

106
00:06:25,677 --> 00:06:30,140
Yeah. I think you'll probably get
a call or email too, so you handle it—

107
00:06:30,224 --> 00:06:30,849
You handle it—

108
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:31,850
Ah, sorry.

109
00:06:31,934 --> 00:06:33,560
Ah... what's wrong?

110
00:06:33,644 --> 00:06:36,188
Well, my phone battery is dying.

111
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:38,357
I'm at the police station now,

112
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,567
but I'll call again
when I get back to the hotel.

113
00:06:40,818 --> 00:06:45,155
So you said those characters
might mean "call"?

114
00:06:45,239 --> 00:06:49,451
Yeah. The police and
Miyama-san's three friends

115
00:06:49,535 --> 00:06:51,662
said they could understand that.

116
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:55,457
But since that message
can't identify the culprit,

117
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,918
we decided to go back
to the hotel for now.

118
00:06:58,001 --> 00:07:00,629
Hey hey, be careful.

119
00:07:00,712 --> 00:07:03,173
The bag-snatcher might
still be lurking around...

120
00:07:03,257 --> 00:07:05,759
It's fine, it's fine.

121
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:08,512
Ah... This time, I asked Kanou-san

122
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:10,597
to drive me and your wife
back to the hotel.

123
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:12,182
Wife...

124
00:07:12,266 --> 00:07:14,685
Wh... who's this Kanou?

125
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:16,728
You heard Ran mention him earlier,

126
00:07:16,812 --> 00:07:20,065
Miyama-san's handsome friend. Handsome!

127
00:07:20,149 --> 00:07:21,191
Sonoko.

128
00:07:21,275 --> 00:07:23,610
It's fine, it's the truth.

129
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:26,405
The other two friends
are together too, right?

130
00:07:26,488 --> 00:07:28,574
Ah... it seems like it's just Kanou-san.

131
00:07:28,991 --> 00:07:32,161
The deceased Miyama-san's lover,
Yanuma-san,

132
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:34,288
is taking a long time for questioning,

133
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:38,750
and Kanou-san was just waiting
in his car for that to finish.

134
00:07:39,084 --> 00:07:41,753
It seems Bito-san went back
to the hotel first.

135
00:07:41,837 --> 00:07:46,592
Yanuma-san's questioning seems
like it'll take more time, so—

136
00:07:46,675 --> 00:07:51,013
Kanou-san said he'd drop us
at the hotel and then come back.

137
00:07:51,096 --> 00:07:52,306
Ah, I see.

138
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:55,309
Well, I'll hang up.
My battery is really dying.

139
00:07:55,392 --> 00:07:56,435
Ah...

140
00:07:56,768 --> 00:07:57,769
...geez.

141
00:07:58,729 --> 00:08:01,481
I should have gone to the beach too.

142
00:08:01,565 --> 00:08:02,566
Beach?

143
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:06,320
Speaking of the beach, Ayumi,
I found a jellyfish!

144
00:08:06,403 --> 00:08:08,488
What are you saying, Ayumi-chan?

145
00:08:08,572 --> 00:08:11,783
There's no way there are jellyfish
in the mountains like this.

146
00:08:11,867 --> 00:08:13,577
There are! Huh?

147
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:16,580
Look, over there.

148
00:08:19,166 --> 00:08:21,168
Really?

149
00:08:21,418 --> 00:08:24,922
Huh? See, a jellyfish.

150
00:08:26,465 --> 00:08:28,258
I... indeed.

151
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:32,679
If you turn the hot spring mark
upside down, it looks like a jellyfish.

152
00:08:32,763 --> 00:08:34,431
See? Oh, it's a jellyfish!

153
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,308
I can see it.

154
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:43,440
If you turn the hot spring mark
upside down, it looks like a jellyfish.

155
00:08:50,364 --> 00:08:53,283
I see. So that's it.

156
00:08:55,786 --> 00:08:58,789
So it means lie down and wash your face.

157
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:03,543
I can't believe I

158
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:07,297
was stumped by such a simple code.

159
00:09:08,131 --> 00:09:11,885
Well, sometimes these simple codes
are unexpectedly harder to solve...

160
00:09:14,471 --> 00:09:20,227
Professor, isn't it fine now?
Please tell us the answer to the code.

161
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:22,688
What is "Marumushini Tento"?

162
00:09:22,938 --> 00:09:25,440
Hahahaha, well...

163
00:09:25,524 --> 00:09:29,736
No. I can't tell you
until everyone gives up.

164
00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:32,739
Then I give up,
so secretly tell only me.

165
00:09:32,823 --> 00:09:34,324
That's cheating, Genta-kun.

166
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:35,951
Why is Ran...

167
00:09:36,034 --> 00:09:38,245
Hey, Conan-kun. Huh?

168
00:09:38,829 --> 00:09:40,330
You still haven't solved it?

169
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:46,336
Ah... yeah, I'm completely clueless.

170
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:48,839
Then just give up already.

171
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:51,842
Conan-kun, you're being a sore loser.

172
00:09:52,551 --> 00:09:55,095
You guys give up too easily.

173
00:09:55,387 --> 00:09:57,180
Hahahaha.

174
00:09:57,264 --> 00:10:00,309
It seems even Shinichi
hasn't solved it yet.

175
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:04,813
Anyway, let's think carefully
from the start.

176
00:10:06,565 --> 00:10:09,443
First, these characters
written only in katakana.

177
00:10:10,027 --> 00:10:12,904
I understand "Marumushi" and "Tento"
being in katakana,

178
00:10:13,238 --> 00:10:16,908
but don't you think it's strange that
the "Ni" in between is also in katakana?

179
00:10:16,992 --> 00:10:18,410
Th... that's true.

180
00:10:18,493 --> 00:10:23,457
Second, if you look closely,
the balance of each character is oddly off.

181
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:24,666
You're right.

182
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:28,045
But isn't that just because
the Professor's handwriting is bad?

183
00:10:28,378 --> 00:10:29,880
Hahahahaha...

184
00:10:30,714 --> 00:10:31,923
And thirdly—

185
00:10:32,424 --> 00:10:34,801
the hints from the Professor and Haibara.

186
00:10:34,885 --> 00:10:36,136
Eh?

187
00:10:36,219 --> 00:10:38,221
Did they give hints?

188
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:42,642
Yeah. Saying "think carefully
while lying down" and—

189
00:10:43,101 --> 00:10:46,104
"if you don't get it, wash your face
and start over"—

190
00:10:46,605 --> 00:10:49,358
are things the Professor and Haibara
don't usually say.

191
00:10:49,441 --> 00:10:51,318
They're clearly hints.

192
00:10:51,401 --> 00:10:55,364
Maybe it means to lie down
and look at these characters.

193
00:10:55,447 --> 00:10:56,448
Ah... Okay!

194
00:10:57,991 --> 00:11:00,160
So we just lie down, right?

195
00:11:01,995 --> 00:11:03,580
Hmm...

196
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:08,585
Nothing different... ah!

197
00:11:09,127 --> 00:11:10,962
Wh... what is it, Genta-kun?

198
00:11:11,046 --> 00:11:12,631
Did you figure something out?

199
00:11:12,714 --> 00:11:13,840
Ah...

200
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:18,345
Ah... ah? Ah... oh?

201
00:11:18,637 --> 00:11:21,348
Oh, Genta-kun, what is it?

202
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:25,185
Ah... no, I feel like I almost got it...

203
00:11:25,268 --> 00:11:26,353
"Almost"?

204
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,063
Be clear!

205
00:11:28,146 --> 00:11:31,900
Shut up! When I laid down,
I felt like I could read it.

206
00:11:31,983 --> 00:11:34,486
Whew, close, close.

207
00:11:34,569 --> 00:11:35,654
No.

208
00:11:36,029 --> 00:11:40,409
That hateful, smug face
with the loosening lips.

209
00:11:41,284 --> 00:11:43,495
Probably, he has already...

210
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,580
Huh?

211
00:11:45,664 --> 00:11:50,085
Hmm, even sideways,
I can't think of anything.

212
00:11:50,168 --> 00:11:51,586
Yeah...

213
00:11:51,962 --> 00:11:55,382
Well then, let's try the other hint.

214
00:11:55,465 --> 00:11:59,845
Hmm? The other one,
the "wash your face" one?

215
00:11:59,928 --> 00:12:03,682
But telling us to wash our faces
in the mountains...

216
00:12:03,765 --> 00:12:09,396
Ah, could it mean to soak
in the hot water of that inn?

217
00:12:09,896 --> 00:12:13,024
No way. Both Haibara and
the Professor said it:

218
00:12:13,108 --> 00:12:14,901
there's nothing at that inn.

219
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:17,279
Then where are we supposed to wash?

220
00:12:17,362 --> 00:12:18,363
That's right.

221
00:12:18,655 --> 00:12:22,492
Beats me. Maybe it's not actually
washing your face—

222
00:12:22,576 --> 00:12:25,620
but related to something
you do when washing your face.

223
00:12:25,704 --> 00:12:28,915
Huh? First, turn the faucet...

224
00:12:28,999 --> 00:12:31,126
Splash water on your face...

225
00:12:31,209 --> 00:12:33,628
Dry your face with a towel...

226
00:12:33,712 --> 00:12:35,338
...and then?

227
00:12:35,422 --> 00:12:36,590
And then...

228
00:12:36,673 --> 00:12:38,884
Um... Hmm.

229
00:12:40,552 --> 00:12:42,262
Let's eat!

230
00:12:42,596 --> 00:12:46,016
Genta-kun, we're talking
about washing your face!

231
00:12:46,475 --> 00:12:48,643
After you wash your face, you eat, right?

232
00:12:48,727 --> 00:12:50,020
A mirror. Huh?

233
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:52,439
After that, you look in the mirror.

234
00:12:52,522 --> 00:12:57,027
A mirror? Looking at that,
all you see is your own face.

235
00:12:57,110 --> 00:12:59,279
It's getting more confusing.

236
00:12:59,362 --> 00:13:02,991
But I think the mirror is a good clue. Look,

237
00:13:03,450 --> 00:13:06,870
like that hot spring mark,
if you turn it upside down,

238
00:13:07,204 --> 00:13:10,123
it can look like
a completely different jellyfish.

239
00:13:10,415 --> 00:13:12,709
Eh? Even if you turn it upside down—

240
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,961
it doesn't look like
a sea bream or flounder.

241
00:13:15,587 --> 00:13:17,631
And I can't read the characters.

242
00:13:17,714 --> 00:13:18,798
Wait a minute.

243
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:23,094
Could it be that
"lie down and wash your face" means...

244
00:13:23,637 --> 00:13:27,140
turn the vertical characters sideways
and reflect them in a mirror?

245
00:13:27,224 --> 00:13:31,061
Lay them sideways, flip them,
instead of reflecting them in a mirror...

246
00:13:43,615 --> 00:13:44,908
Ah.

247
00:13:44,991 --> 00:13:46,826
Ah...

248
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:51,331
"Mura Matsuri no Torii."

249
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:54,459
Village festival's shrine gate.

250
00:13:54,793 --> 00:13:56,670
Oh? That shrine.

251
00:13:57,045 --> 00:13:59,673
Right? Professor, Ai-chan.

252
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:01,967
Ding dong.

253
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:05,428
Correct! Hahahaha!

254
00:14:05,512 --> 00:14:07,639
Alright! We did it!

255
00:14:07,722 --> 00:14:10,308
We did it! Ahahahaha!

256
00:14:10,392 --> 00:14:11,851
Let's go right away.

257
00:14:11,935 --> 00:14:13,853
Okay. Yeah! The treasure!

258
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:18,191
Oh my, a self-satisfied look,

259
00:14:18,275 --> 00:14:22,279
as if to say they taught the children
that they can do it if they try.

260
00:14:22,571 --> 00:14:25,198
Ah, pretty handsome, right?

261
00:14:25,407 --> 00:14:27,534
Hmm? Phew.

262
00:14:28,577 --> 00:14:31,288
More importantly,
aren't you going to see, Shinichi?

263
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:33,540
I'm sure you want to know
what the treasure is.

264
00:14:33,999 --> 00:14:36,418
I don't need to see something like that.

265
00:14:36,501 --> 00:14:40,880
The location indicated by the code
is the shrine gate that's lit up at night—

266
00:14:40,964 --> 00:14:43,216
that shrine's torii gate.

267
00:14:49,264 --> 00:14:52,559
If they smear tree sap
on the pillars of that torii gate...

268
00:14:53,727 --> 00:14:55,895
they'll come swarming.

269
00:14:55,979 --> 00:14:57,689
Ah, found them!

270
00:14:57,772 --> 00:15:00,692
Wow! Amazing!

271
00:15:01,151 --> 00:15:03,153
Beetles and stag beetles.

272
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:06,072
Hah, that's right.

273
00:15:07,532 --> 00:15:08,950
Still,

274
00:15:10,535 --> 00:15:12,954
this code was well thought out.

275
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:16,082
It can be read both forwards and backwards.

276
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,543
It's thanks to Ai-kun.

277
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:22,672
At first, I thought about
making it an animal code.

278
00:15:23,048 --> 00:15:27,260
I was thinking of various things,
like putting paper with animal names

279
00:15:27,344 --> 00:15:29,220
on a windowpane.

280
00:15:29,512 --> 00:15:33,433
Ai-kun, watching from outside,
said to me,

281
00:15:33,516 --> 00:15:36,770
"Isn't 'Sanso' too difficult for children?"

282
00:15:37,479 --> 00:15:38,772
...he said.

283
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:40,148
I see.

284
00:15:40,231 --> 00:15:43,693
When you look at the characters "Kirin"
from the back, they look like "Sanso"—

285
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:46,071
and that's how I came up with the code...

286
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:47,697
Eh?

287
00:15:48,198 --> 00:15:49,532
Shinichi?

288
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:51,785
Glass...

289
00:15:53,203 --> 00:15:54,245
Back...

290
00:15:54,829 --> 00:15:56,206
Transparent...

291
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:58,500
Wait a minute.

292
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,585
Th... this is...

293
00:16:02,587 --> 00:16:04,589
Damn... is that it?

294
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:08,677
So that's how it was.

295
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:11,471
That's why Ran's face
crossed my mind earlier.

296
00:16:11,554 --> 00:16:14,516
Ran is... Ran is in danger!

297
00:16:22,023 --> 00:16:25,151
♪~ (cell phone ringing) ~♪

298
00:16:26,069 --> 00:16:29,531
Ah, Shinichi? Where are you now...

299
00:16:29,614 --> 00:16:31,157
I told you earlier.

300
00:16:31,241 --> 00:16:33,535
We're heading back to the hotel
in Kanou-san's car.

301
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:36,454
Eh? Get out of this car right now?

302
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:39,958
I figured out the real meaning of "teiu."

303
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:43,253
Before the "t" in "teiu,"

304
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:46,464
there was actually a small dot
like a punctuation mark written.

305
00:16:46,798 --> 00:16:49,175
Turn it vertically and flip it over.

306
00:16:49,259 --> 00:16:51,261
The culprit's name...

307
00:16:52,429 --> 00:16:56,599
Hey, Ran! Ran... Ran!

308
00:16:57,392 --> 00:17:00,353
Ah... the battery died.

309
00:17:00,437 --> 00:17:01,813
What did he say, dear?

310
00:17:01,896 --> 00:17:04,441
Oh, Sonoko. Ah...

311
00:17:04,524 --> 00:17:09,028
What does "get out of the car,
turn it vertically, and flip it over" mean?

312
00:17:10,155 --> 00:17:12,198
He's not lying, is he?

313
00:17:12,282 --> 00:17:14,576
Fufufu. No way...

314
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:21,166
Eh? Ran and Sonoko
are caught up in an incident?

315
00:17:21,249 --> 00:17:24,169
Yeah, Sonoko saw it.

316
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:27,213
The characters written by the man
murdered in the hotel room.

317
00:17:27,297 --> 00:17:28,798
Ch... characters?

318
00:17:28,882 --> 00:17:32,427
They were written horizontally
in lowercase letters: "teiu."

319
00:17:33,011 --> 00:17:36,097
To be precise, there was a dot
before the "t,"

320
00:17:36,181 --> 00:17:37,682
the "i" was closer to an "l,"

321
00:17:37,766 --> 00:17:39,851
and the "u" was closer
to the hiragana "shi."

322
00:17:40,602 --> 00:17:42,812
It's the same as the village festival's
shrine gate.

323
00:17:43,271 --> 00:17:47,776
If you take those horizontally written
characters, turn them vertically,
and look from the back?

324
00:17:48,818 --> 00:17:50,445
It becomes "Marumushini Tento."

325
00:17:50,528 --> 00:17:52,822
If you take "Sanso" vertically
and look from the back?

326
00:17:53,156 --> 00:17:54,157
It becomes "Kirin."

327
00:17:54,491 --> 00:17:56,409
So what about "teiu"?

328
00:17:58,036 --> 00:17:59,412
Ah, that is...

329
00:18:00,121 --> 00:18:02,248
It becomes "Kanou."

330
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:03,750
Ah.

331
00:18:04,209 --> 00:18:05,710
Kanou?

332
00:18:07,003 --> 00:18:08,004
Oh!

333
00:18:08,463 --> 00:18:10,465
But why leave such a hard-to-understand—

334
00:18:10,548 --> 00:18:14,219
dying message like a code?

335
00:18:14,302 --> 00:18:16,012
It's not a code or anything.

336
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:19,307
The victim, lying on the floor,

337
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:22,060
wrote those characters
on the window glass from inside the room,

338
00:18:22,143 --> 00:18:25,772
and Sonoko just saw them
from outside the window.

339
00:18:26,022 --> 00:18:29,526
Then we need to tell Ran and the others
about this right away.

340
00:18:30,193 --> 00:18:33,238
Even if we want to tell them,
Ran's phone is dead.

341
00:18:33,321 --> 00:18:38,368
And on top of that, Ran and Sonoko
are in that man Kanou's car right now.

342
00:18:47,043 --> 00:18:50,964
Hey, isn't this different from
the road to the hotel?

343
00:18:51,047 --> 00:18:53,883
It's fine. It's a shortcut.

344
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:57,887
Hey, where is the hotel
those two are staying at?

345
00:18:57,971 --> 00:19:01,599
If I knew that,
I'd contact the nearby police.

346
00:19:01,683 --> 00:19:04,894
I heard they went to the beach,
but I don't know where...

347
00:19:04,978 --> 00:19:07,897
Damn. I should have realized sooner.

348
00:19:08,231 --> 00:19:10,817
When I received that strange email
from Sonoko's phone,

349
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:13,987
which should have been snatched,

350
00:19:14,863 --> 00:19:18,408
the photo email sent to my phone
showed that dying message.

351
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:20,410
He wanted to erase it,

352
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:23,788
so he emailed me to ask
for my address and name.

353
00:19:24,914 --> 00:19:26,916
Wait, that means...

354
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,334
Hee~

355
00:19:28,418 --> 00:19:32,422
So that Shinichi-kun you mentioned
is a high school detective?

356
00:19:32,505 --> 00:19:33,923
Yes, I suppose.

357
00:19:34,007 --> 00:19:36,759
Amazing. Having a detective as a boyfriend.

358
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:40,138
Ah... no, he's not my boyfriend or...

359
00:19:40,221 --> 00:19:42,557
They're so lovey-dovey, it's embarrassing.

360
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:44,225
That's why earlier today,

361
00:19:44,309 --> 00:19:48,521
she sent him a photo mail
of her in her swimsuit.

362
00:19:48,813 --> 00:19:50,273
Hey, Sonoko.

363
00:19:50,356 --> 00:19:52,233
Fufufu.

364
00:19:52,317 --> 00:19:53,776
But that's too bad.

365
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:55,987
Shinichi-kun isn't here, is he?

366
00:19:56,279 --> 00:19:59,657
I wanted to meet that famous detective.

367
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,243
Sonoko... Right about now,

368
00:20:02,327 --> 00:20:05,204
he's probably rubbing his cheek
against that photo mail, isn't he?

369
00:20:05,288 --> 00:20:09,208
♪~ (cell phone ringing) ~♪

370
00:20:09,792 --> 00:20:12,211
If the culprit is waiting
for me to contact him,

371
00:20:12,545 --> 00:20:15,965
he should be carrying Sonoko's phone
with the power on.

372
00:20:16,507 --> 00:20:20,720
Please realize it. That man is the murderer.

373
00:20:20,803 --> 00:20:22,555
♪~ (cell phone ringing) ~♪

374
00:20:22,639 --> 00:20:26,184
Huh? That ringtone
is the same as Sonoko's phone.

375
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:30,063
Come to think of it, that's my...

376
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:32,523
You're right.

377
00:20:32,607 --> 00:20:34,734
Huh? But... why?

378
00:20:34,817 --> 00:20:36,945
Heh. That's right.

379
00:20:37,695 --> 00:20:41,449
Because I snatched it from you earlier.

380
00:20:41,532 --> 00:20:42,784
Eh?

381
00:20:44,661 --> 00:20:47,455
To erase the evidence of the murder.

382
00:20:47,538 --> 00:20:48,957
Ehh?

383
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:53,836
Now, let's go further in
and have a nice, long talk.

384
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:57,340
And also about where that kid Shinichi is.

385
00:21:00,426 --> 00:21:01,135
Still not connecting?

386
00:21:01,135 --> 00:21:02,428
♪~ (phone ringing) ~♪

387
00:21:02,512 --> 00:21:03,554
Just be quiet.

388
00:21:03,638 --> 00:21:05,264
Ah, well...

389
00:21:06,516 --> 00:21:07,517
(Connection sound)

390
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,851
Connected.

391
00:21:09,227 --> 00:21:11,270
Hello? Hello?

392
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:13,898
Hello?

393
00:21:15,316 --> 00:21:21,322
♪~♪

394
00:22:33,811 --> 00:22:39,817
♪~♪

395
00:22:39,901 --> 00:22:42,070
Don't "hello" me.

396
00:22:42,153 --> 00:22:44,947
What were you doing
while Ran was in danger?

397
00:22:45,156 --> 00:22:47,617
Hey, are you listening? You...

398
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:48,951
Ah, no, what do you mean...

399
00:22:49,035 --> 00:22:52,497
We had a hard time over here
when the car crashed into a tree!

400
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:55,833
Huh? The car hit a tree? Why?

401
00:22:55,917 --> 00:22:58,377
What do you mean, why? We had no choice.

402
00:22:58,461 --> 00:23:01,964
Ran's side kick exploded
right in the face of the murderer

403
00:23:02,048 --> 00:23:05,343
who was driving!

404
00:23:05,593 --> 00:23:07,637
Ah... I see.

405
00:23:09,931 --> 00:23:13,184
After that, the police Sonoko called arrived,

406
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:15,561
and the culprit was apprehended.

407
00:23:16,646 --> 00:23:22,068
The motive for the murder was that
his friends found out he bought his way
into university and threatened him.

408
00:23:22,819 --> 00:23:24,278
To cover up his crime,

409
00:23:24,362 --> 00:23:28,658
he committed an even greater crime—
a classic pattern.

410
00:23:30,326 --> 00:23:31,661
And...

411
00:23:31,869 --> 00:23:32,870
Huh?

412
00:23:33,162 --> 00:23:35,665
I thought I saved it here...

413
00:23:35,748 --> 00:23:37,291
Hmm? Oh.

414
00:23:37,375 --> 00:23:40,586
I deleted that woman's swimsuit photo.

415
00:23:40,670 --> 00:23:42,964
Huh... huh? Why?

416
00:23:43,339 --> 00:23:46,676
Why? Because it's against the law.

417
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:50,304
Sorry. I asked Ai-chan to delete it.

418
00:23:51,097 --> 00:23:52,723
Ha... Haibara?

419
00:23:53,307 --> 00:23:54,308
(Yawn)

420
00:23:54,392 --> 00:23:55,518
You little...

421
00:23:55,893 --> 00:23:58,187
Damn!

422
00:24:01,774 --> 00:24:05,187
Next Conan's Hint: "The two cups"

423
00:24:05,818 --> 00:24:07,686
What's the title of the next episode?

424
00:24:07,770 --> 00:24:10,430
It's half of the complete,
so if eel over rice is used as an analogy...

425
00:24:10,514 --> 00:24:11,514
Huh?
